The '''Academia Dominicana de la Lengua [http://www.academia.org.do]''' (variously translated as the '''Dominican Academy of Language''', the '''Dominican Academy of the Language''', the '''Dominican Academy of Letters''', or glossed as the '''Dominican Academy of the Spanish Language'''; acronym '''ADL''') is the [[Dominican Republic]]'s [[Association of Spanish Language Academies|correspondent academy]] of the [[Real Academia Española|Royal Spanish Academy]]. It was founded in [[Santo Domingo]] on 12 October 1927 and, like the other academies, has the principal function of working to regulate the [[Spanish language]].
