'''Arwa Saleh''' (1951-1997) was an Egyptian feminist activist and student leader in the 1970s. In 1997 she committed suicide by jumping from a tenth floor apartment.<ref>[http://thecairopost.youm7.com/news/70908/inside_egypt/the-most-famous-people-who-committed-suicide-in-egypt The most famous people who committed suicide in Egypt], ''The Cairo Post'', Jan 11, 2014.</ref> The event is given fictional treatment in [[Radwa Ashour]]'s 2008 novel ''Release'',<ref name="Al-Arian2014">{{cite book|author=Abdullah Al-Arian|title=Answering the Call: Popular Islamic Activism in Sadats Egypt|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OEuPAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA221|year=2014|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-993128-6|page=221}}</ref> as well as [[Youssef Rakha]]'s 2014 novel ''The Crocodiles''.<ref>Ibrahim Farghali, [http://chimurengachronic.co.za/the-undeveloped-intellectual-in-zombie-land/ The Undeveloped Intellectual in Zombie-land], March 19, 2015</ref>
==Works== * ''al-Mubtasarun'' [The Premature Ones], 1996. Translated into Engish by [[Samah Selim]], 2016.
