{{one source|date=August 2017}} {{primary sources|date=August 2017}} {{Infobox school | name = V Gymnasium | native_name = V. gimnazija | image = Peta Gimnazija u Zagrebu.JPG | alt = | motto = | motto_translation = | address = Klaićeva 1 | city = [[Zagreb]] | postalcode = 10000 | country = [[Croatia]] | coordinates = {{Coord|45|48|32|N|15|58|0|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | type = | established = {{Start date and age|1938|11|07|df=yes}} | founder = | headmaster = Tihomir Engesfeld, dr.sc. | grades = | enrolment = | students = | pupils = 900 | classes = 28 | language = [[Croatian language|Croatian]] | hours_in_day = 7 averagely (varies from 6 to 9/10) | classrooms = 18 (+ 5 cabinets + 4 staff rooms + 8 other rooms) | colours = Green | nickname = Peta | song = | publication = | newspaper = | graduates = | graduates_year = 2012/2013 | website = {{URL|www.petagimnazija.hr}} | footnotes = }}
'''The Fifth Gymnasium''' ({{lang-hr|V. gimnazija, Peta gimnazija}}) is a high school in [[Zagreb]], [[Croatia]] specialising in science and mathematics. It opened its doors on 7 November 1938. Today it has about 900 students in 28 classes.
Students have taken part in the [[International Mathematical Olympiad]] and the [[International Chemistry Olympiad]], where they have received various medals, and also the [[International Physics Olympiad]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.petagimnazija.hr |title=School information |accessdate=2008-01-21 |work=Peta Gimnazija |language=Croatian}}</ref>
